om":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20 g","calories":"1422 kJ \/ 340 kcal"},"usefulItems":"casserole dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Make the paptert a day ahead and keep in the fridge until needed. Finish in the oven just before serving.","Leftovers will keep well in the fridge until the following day. Reheat before serving.","For a vegetarian version, try replacing the biltong with sautéed vegetables.","Experiment by using your favourite cheese for this recipe. Cheddar, Gouda, mozzarella and blue cheese will all work well.","Biltong is a form of dried, cured meat that originated in South Africa. Various types of meat are used to produce it, ranging from beef and game meats, to fillets of ostrich from commercial farms.<br>Paptert (porridge pie) is a delicious modern addition to a South African barbeque (braai). It resembles a lasagne but is made from maize porridge (mieliepap) and includes a generous vegetable filling which ensures a rich, moist and decadent savoury tart."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 15m","8 portions"]}